{"content": "I need to multiply 8a0 \u00d7 779 in base 11.\n\n**Step 1: Convert 8a0 (base 11) to base 10**\n- 8a0\u2081\u2081 = 8\u00d711\u00b2 + 10\u00d711\u00b9 + 0\u00d711\u2070\n- = 8\u00d7121 + 10\u00d711 + 0\n- = 968 + 110 + 0\n- = 1078\u2081\u2080\n\n**Step 2: Convert 779 (base 11) to base 10**\n- 779\u2081\u2081 = 7\u00d711\u00b2 + 7\u00d711\u00b9 + 9\u00d711\u2070\n- = 7\u00d7121 + 7\u00d711 + 9\n- = 847 + 77 + 9\n- = 933\u2081\u2080\n\n**Step 3: Multiply in base 10**\n- 1078 \u00d7 933 = 1,005,774\u2081\u2080\n\n**Step 4: Convert 1,005,774 (base 10) to base 11**\n- 1,005,774 \u00f7 11 = 91,434 R 0\n- 91,434 \u00f7 11 = 8,312 R 2\n- 8,312 \u00f7 11 = 755 R 7\n- 755 \u00f7 11 = 68 R 7\n- 68 \u00f7 11 = 6 R 2\n- 6 \u00f7 11 = 0 R 6\n\nReading remainders from bottom to top: 627720\n\n627720", "model": "anthropic/claude-sonnet-4.5", "prompt_tokens": 365, "completion_tokens": 405}